import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.countplot(x='key', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of food and drink categories in the University District area?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Food and Drink Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Categories', loc='upper right', labels=data['key'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of latitude values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat_shifted', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_lat_shifted = data['lat_shifted'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_lat_shifted, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_lat_shifted:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of shifted latitude values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
